# https://machinelearningmastery.com/custom-metrics-deep-learning-keras-python/
# https://github.com/keras-team/keras/blob/master/keras/metrics.py
def acc_sign(y_true, y_pred):
    if mode == 'mxnet':
        return (np.sign(y_pred).flatten() == y_true).sum() / len(y_true)
    elif mode == 'keras':
        return K.mean(K.equal(K.sign(y_pred), y_true), axis=-1)

def acc_round(y_true, y_pred):
    # each interval for class -1, 0, 1 must have a width of 2/3 to be equally distributed
    # therefore you must convert (1/3) to (1/2) and only then round to the closest integer
    # 1/3 * x = 1/2
    return K.mean(K.equal(K.round(y_pred * 1.5), y_true), axis=-1)

metrics = []

metrics.append(mx.metric.CrossEntropy(name='policy_loss', output_names=['policy_output'], label_names=['policy_label']))

metrics.append(mx.metric.create(acc_sign, name='value_acc_sign', output_names=['value_output'], label_names=['value_label']))
metrics.append(mx.metric.Accuracy(axis=1, name='policy_acc', output_names=['policy_output'], label_names=['policy_label']))

def log_metrics(metrics, global_step, prefix='train_'):
    for metric in metrics:                  # show the metric stats
        print(' - %s%s: %.4f' % (prefix, metric.get()[0], metric.get()[1]), end="")
        # add the metrics to the tensorboard event file
        sw.add_scalar(tag=prefix+metric.get()[0], value=metric.get()[1], global_step=global_step)

def train(mod, nb_parts, val_iter, sw, nb_k_steps=200, patience = 25, batch_steps = 1000,  k_steps_initial=0):
    
    t_s = time()
    # set a custom seed for reproducability
    #random.seed(42)

    # define a list which describes the order of the processed batches
    ordering = list(range(nb_parts))

    # keep track on how many batches have been processed in this epoch so far 
    batch_proc_tmp = 0
    # counter for thousands steps
    k_steps = k_steps_initial
    k_steps_end = k_steps_initial + nb_k_steps
    
    val_loss_best = None
    k_steps_best = None
    val_p_acc_best = None
    
    patience_cnt = 0
    epoch = 1
    
    reset_metrics(metrics)

    while(True):
        # reshuffle the ordering of the training game batches (shuffle works in place)
        random.shuffle(ordering)

        logging.info("EPOCH %d", epoch)
        logging.info("=========================")
        t_s_steps = time()

        for part_id in tqdm_notebook(ordering):

            # load one chunk of the dataset from memory
            s_idcs_train, x_train, yv_train, yp_train, pgn_datasets_train = load_pgn_dataset(part_id=part_id, normalize=normalize, verbose=False)
            # update the train iter object
            train_iter = mx.io.NDArrayIter({data_name: x_train}, {'value_label': yv_train, 'policy_label': yp_train.argmax(axis=1)}, batch_size) 

            train_iter.reset()

            for i, batch in enumerate(train_iter):
                mod.forward(batch, is_train=True)       # compute predictions
                for metric in metrics:                  # update the metrics
                        mod.update_metric(metric, batch.label)
                
                mod.backward()                          # compute gradients
                mod.update()                            # update parameters

                batch_proc_tmp += 1

                # show metrics every thousands steps
                if batch_proc_tmp >= batch_steps:
                    ms_step = ((time() - t_s_steps) / batch_steps) * 1000

                    logging.info("Step %dK/%dK - %dms/step", k_steps, k_steps_end, ms_step)
                    logging.info("-------------------------")
                    
                    k_steps += 1
                    patience_cnt += 1

                    # show the metrics on the current training set
                    log_metrics(metrics, k_steps, prefix='train_')

                    # measure performance on validation data
                    reset_metrics(metrics)
                    val_iter.reset()
                    score = mod.score(val_iter, metrics)

                    # calculate the current val_loss
                    val_loss = 0.01 * score[0][1]+ 0.99 * score[1][1]
                    val_p_acc = score[3][1]
                    
                    # print out and save the validation performance
                    log_metrics(metrics, k_steps, prefix='val_')
                    
                    # update batch_proc_tmp counter by subtracting the batch_steps
                    batch_proc_tmp = batch_proc_tmp - batch_steps

                    # check if a new checkpoint shall be created
                    if val_loss_best is None or val_loss < val_loss_best:
                        # update val_loss_best
                        val_loss_best = val_loss
                        val_p_acc_best = val_p_acc
                        k_steps_best = k_steps
                        
                        prefix ="./weights/model-%.5f-%.5f" % (val_loss_best, val_p_acc_best)
                        mod.save_checkpoint(prefix=prefix, epoch=k_steps)
                        # reset the patience counter
                        patience_cnt = 0
                        
                    # print the elapsed time
                    t_delta = time() - t_s_steps
                    print(" - %.ds" % t_delta)
                    t_s_steps = time()
                    
                    # to continue training stats with reseted metrics
                    reset_metrics(metrics)                    

                    if patience_cnt >= patience or k_steps == k_steps_end:
                        sw.close()
                        # no progress hasn't been achieved in the desired patience interval
                        # or the maximum number of k_steps has been reached
                        # -> stop training
                        print('Elapsed time for training(hh:mm:ss): ' + str(datetime.timedelta(seconds=round(time() - t_s))))            
                        return (k_steps, val_loss, val_p_acc), (k_steps_best, val_loss_best, val_p_acc_best)
                    
        # increase the current epoch
        epoch += 1

def predict_single(net, x):
    
    if mode == 'keras':
        pred = net.predict(np.expand_dims(x, axis=0))
    elif mode == 'mxnet':
        out = [None, None]
        pred = net(mx.nd.array(np.expand_dims(x, axis=0), ctx=ctx))
        #pred = mod.forward(mx.nd.array(np.expand_dims(x, axis=0)), is_train=False)
        out[0] = pred[0].asnumpy()
        out[1] = pred[1].asnumpy()
    
    return out

Evaluate Performance¶

In [54]:
def eval_pos(net, x_mate, yp_mate, verbose=False):
    
    board = get_board_of_current_mat(x_mate, normalized_input=normalize)
    if verbose is True:
        print("{0}'s turn".format(chess.COLOR_NAMES[board.turn]))
        print("black/white {0}".format(board.pockets))
    pred = predict_single(net, x_mate)

    true_mat = yp_mate.reshape(78,8,8)
    true_move = filter_moves(board, true_mat, is_white_to_move=board.turn, renormalize_confidences=False)[0][0]
    
    pred_mat = pred[1][0].reshape(78,8,8)
    opts = 5
    pred_moves = filter_moves(board, pred_mat, is_white_to_move=board.turn, renormalize_confidences=False)[0][:opts]

    legal_move_cnt = board.legal_moves.count()
    mate_move_cnt = str(board.legal_moves).count('#')
    
    is_mate_5_top = False
    
    for pred_move in pred_moves:
        board_5_top = deepcopy(board)
        board_5_top.push(pred_move)
        if board_5_top.is_checkmate() is True:
            is_mate_5_top = True
            break
    
    board.push(pred_moves[0])
    
    is_checkmate = False
    if board.is_checkmate() is True:
        is_checkmate = True
        
    filtered_pred = sorted(pred[1][0], reverse=True)
    
    if verbose is True:
        plt.barh(range(opts)[::-1], filtered_pred[:opts])
        ax = plt.gca()
        ax.set_yticks(range(opts)[::-1])
        ax.set_yticklabels(pred_moves)
        plt.title('True Move:' + str(true_move) +
                 '\nEval:' + str(pred[0][0]))
        plt.show()
    
    return pred, pred_moves, true_move, board, is_checkmate, is_mate_5_top, legal_move_cnt, mate_move_cnt
